## Rationale
Using only ASCII characters ensures maximum compatibility across different operating systems, version control systems, and development tools. It prevents potential issues with character encoding and makes the codebase more portable.

## Implementation
When creating new files or renaming existing ones:
1. Use only standard ASCII characters (a-z, A-Z, 0-9, and hyphens)
2. Avoid Unicode characters, emojis, or special symbols
3. Keep filenames simple and descriptive
